                <body xml:id="ch4.sc4.1.00120">                        
                                <p><hi rend="initialcap">C</hi>ASE 120.&#8212;<name
                                                type="person" key="667">Private Robert Booth</name>,
                                                <name type="organization" key="649">Co. A, 147th
                                                Pa.</name>; age 21; was admitted <date type="admit"
                                                when="1863-11-04">Nov. 4, 1863</date>, delirious,
                                        with dry tongue and sordes, and on the second day after
                                        admission involuntary discharges from the bowels.  He died on
                                        <date type="death" when="1863-11-13">the 13th</date>.  <hi
                                                rend="italic">Post-mortem</hi> examination showed
                                        &#34;that condition of the intestinal glands usually found in
                                        typhoid cases.&#34;&#8212;<hi rend="italic"><name
                                                  type="person" key="666">Act. Ass't Surg. James
                                                  Robertson</name>, <name type="hospital" key="186">1st Division Hospital</name>, Alexandria,
                                                Va.</hi></p>                        
